casebody.data:
Joshua ARMSTRONG, Appellant/Petitioner(s),
v.
STATE of Florida, Appellee/Respondent(s). CASE NO.: 2D18-0736 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Second District. March 29, 2018

BY ORDER OF THE COURT:

This appeal is dismissed for lack of jurisdiction because the notice of appeal was filed more than 30 days after rendition of the order being appealed and is, therefore, untimely.

MORRIS, SLEET, and BADALAMENTI, JJ., Concur.
